Spire Bank, formerly Equatorial Commercial Bank, has cut its insurance financing rate to eight per cent from 14 per cent for clients of Fidelity Insurance and Invesco Assurance.The bank, which rebranded in July, said the move will enable SMEs and corporates to pay for insurance in a flexible way. The scheme offers our customers the lowest insurance premium financing rates in the market. It has simplified application documentation and is open to premiums as low as Sh25,000 with no maximum limit, Spire Bank managing director Tim Gitonga said. Repayment options will be as low as 3.02 per cent flat rate for 10 months.